The aim of the course with pragmatic orientation is to study grammatical norms of the language.  The main rules of the Russian orthography are studied.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the course is to introduce grammatical norms and norms of pronunciation, morphology, orthography, syntax, accent of Russian literary language.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course a student: 1. has got theoretical knowledge about language norm, and functional diversity of norms, can apply the knowledge in practice; 2. knows history of development of Russian written language; 3. can distinguish between normative and non-normative speech variants; 4. orientates well in normative dictionaries and orthographic study materials; 5. fulfills main norms of the Russian language in her/his oral and written speech.
